      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Combining Best-of-N with Extended Thinking"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Best-of-N and extended thinking are complementary. Extended thinking improves the quality of each individual sample; Best-of-N selects the best among those improved samples. Together they give the highest reliability for hard tasks:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "def sample_with_thinking(prompt: str, budget_tokens: int = 6000) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Generate one sample using extended thinking.\"\"\"\n    response = client.messages.create(\n        model=\"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n        max_tokens=budget_tokens + 4096,\n        thinking={\"type\": \"enabled\", \"budget_tokens\": budget_tokens},\n        temperature=1.0,   # required when thinking is enabled\n        messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": prompt}],\n    )\n    return next(b.text for b in response.content if b.type == \"text\")\n\ndef best_of_n_with_thinking(\n    prompt: str,\n    verifier: Callable[[str], float],\n    n: int = 4,\n    budget_tokens: int = 6000,\n) -> tuple[str, float]:\n    with ThreadPoolExecutor(max_workers=n) as pool:\n        candidates = list(pool.map(\n            lambda _: sample_with_thinking(prompt, budget_tokens),\n            range(n),\n        ))\n\n    scored = [(c, verifier(c)) for c in candidates]\n    return max(scored, key=lambda x: x[1])\n\n# Use case: hard algorithmic problems where accuracy matters more than speed\nanswer, score = best_of_n_with_thinking(\n    prompt=\"Design an efficient algorithm to detect cycles in a directed graph. Prove its correctness.\",\n    verifier=heuristic_verifier,\n    n=3,\n    budget_tokens=8000,\n)\nprint(f\"Score: {score:.2f}\\n{answer[:500]}\")"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Production Pattern: Tiered Verification"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A practical production pattern runs a cheap heuristic verifier first, then escalates to the expensive LLM judge only for candidates that pass the initial filter. This keeps average cost low while maintaining quality:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "def tiered_best_of_n(\n    prompt: str,\n    n: int = 5,\n    heuristic_threshold: float = 0.5,\n) -> tuple[str, float]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Stage 1: fast heuristic filter.\n    Stage 2: LLM judge on survivors only.\n    \"\"\"\n    with ThreadPoolExecutor(max_workers=n) as pool:\n        candidates = list(pool.map(lambda _: sample_once(prompt), range(n)))\n\n    # Stage 1: cheap filter\n    stage1 = [(c, heuristic_verifier(c)) for c in candidates]\n    survivors = [(c, s) for c, s in stage1 if s >= heuristic_threshold]\n\n    if not survivors:\n        # All failed heuristic \u2014 return best heuristic score\n        return max(stage1, key=lambda x: x[1])\n\n    # Stage 2: LLM judge only on survivors\n    judge = llm_judge(prompt)\n    with ThreadPoolExecutor(max_workers=len(survivors)) as pool:\n        final_scores = list(pool.map(lambda cs: (cs[0], judge(cs[0])), survivors))\n\n    return max(final_scores, key=lambda x: x[1])\n\nanswer, score = tiered_best_of_n(\n    \"Write a Python class implementing a min-heap with push and pop operations.\",\n    n=5,\n)\nprint(f\"Final score: {score:.2f}\")\n"
          }
        ]
      },
